Although aid is now trickling into Zimbabwe, boulders from mudslides are still blocking some roads.
Floods washed away bridges that connect a number of the most devastated areas, forcing some military and aid workers to move by foot.
“Some are floating all the way into Mozambique.”Sinyabuwe said that as people fled the worst-hit regions in Zimbabwe, near the border with Mozambique, they were forced to leave behind the dead.
Mozambican President Filipe Nyusi said late Tuesday that more than 200 people died in Mozambique alone.
Beira, Mozambique’s second-largest port, is a major gateway not only to the center of the country but also for landlocked Zimbabwe and Malawi.